{
  "texts": [
    "Fang et al. (2021) proposed a Semantic Context-Induced Attention Fusion Network (SCAFNet), which, through video semantic region segmentation and fusion technology, improved attention prediction for drivers in accident scenarios.",
    "Amini et al. (2023) found through driving behavior simulation that distracted driving significantly impacts driver reaction times and gaze patterns.",
    "Moreover, digital twin and AR technologies can enhance the accuracy and realism of driving behavior simulation, enabling drivers to experience more immersive training in complex scenarios.",
    "This, in turn, significantly improves their ability to respond to unexpected situations and enhances overall driving safety (Calvi et al., 2020; Liao et al., 2023; Wang et al., 2024b).",
    "For instance, VDT technology is utilized to generate virtual vehicles and replicate or extend real vehicle behavior patterns through data-driven and physics-based approaches."
  ]
}